---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — CA Accounting"
  description="Privacy policy for CA Accounting, a Glendale, California-based accounting and tax firm."
>
  <section class="py-20 md:py-24">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-forest font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-6 fade-in">Privacy</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif text-navy leading-tight mb-12 fade-in fade-in-delay-1">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>

        <div class="prose space-y-8 fade-in fade-in-delay-2">
          <p class="text-charcoal-muted text-sm">Last updated: April 2026</p>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">Our commitment</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed">
              CA Accounting is committed to protecting the privacy of every client and prospective client. As a member firm of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (AICPA), we are bound by the AICPA Code of Professional Conduct, which includes specific provisions regarding the confidentiality of client information. This policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your information.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">Information we collect</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
              In the course of providing professional services, we may collect personal and financial information including but not limited to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed space-y-2">
              <li>Name, address, phone number, and email address</li>
              <li>Social Security Number or Taxpayer Identification Number</li>
              <li>Income, expense, and asset information</li>
              <li>Bank and brokerage account details</li>
              <li>Information about your business, employees, and dependents</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">How we use your information</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed">
              We use the information you provide solely to deliver the professional services you engage us for — preparing and filing tax returns, providing accounting and bookkeeping support, advising on financial matters, and communicating with you about our work. We do not sell or rent client information to third parties under any circumstances.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">When we share information</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed">
              We do not disclose client information to anyone outside our firm except as required by law (for example, in response to a court order or IRS subpoena) or with your express consent. When we do share information with your authorization — for example, providing your tax return to a lender — we share only what is necessary for the stated purpose.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">How we protect your information</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed">
              We maintain physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards designed to protect your information. Access to client information is limited to professionals and staff who need it to deliver our services. Sensitive documents are exchanged through encrypted channels — including our secure file portal — rather than ordinary email.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">Website analytics</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed">
              Our website may use standard analytics tools (such as Google Analytics) to understand how visitors use the site. These tools collect non-personally-identifiable information such as pages visited, time on site, and approximate geographic location. This information helps us improve the site and is not connected to any individual client record.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">Your rights</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed">
              You may request a copy of any personal information we hold about you, ask us to correct inaccurate information, or request that we delete information that is no longer required for the services we provide or for legal recordkeeping purposes. To make a request, contact us at the phone number below.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">Changes to this policy</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed">
              We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-navy mb-4">Contact us</h2>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed">
              For questions about this policy or our handling of your information, contact:
            </p>
            <p class="text-charcoal text-base leading-relaxed mt-4">
              CA Accounting<br />
              300 W Glenoaks Blvd, Suite 101<br />
              Glendale, CA 91202<br />
              Phone: <a href="tel:8775009290" class="text-forest hover:text-forest-hover transition-colors">877.500.9290</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
